The paper deals with the problem of navigation in a planar environment using visual object recognition and SLAM techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of visual object recognition techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of an online reactive scheme, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of numerical studies and physical implementation on different platforms suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of avoiding collisions with obstacles, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
